ow Payload titles are resolved at steady state (batched lookup, falls back to local `label`).\n- Where teams are created and how `team_members` is the runtime access truth (not `members.role`).\n\n### Agent 3: Invitations, Access Editing, Finalization\n\n**Question:** How do admins control which learners see which volumes, from invite through post-acceptance through new-volume creation?\n\nRead `src/features/organization/` (invitation-status, invitation-emails, invitation-mutations, member-volume-access), the invite-related action exports in `src/app/(portal)/org/[orgSlug]/actions.ts` (`inviteWithVolumes`, `updateMemberVolumeAccess`, `decideVolumeLearnerSync`, `resendInvitation`), and `src/app/(auth)/org/invite/[invitationId]/page.tsx` plus its `actions.ts`.\n\nReport:\n- The bulk classifier's four buckets (create/refresh/alreadyMember/roleConflict) and where seat enforcement intersects.\n- The `accessScope` lifecycle: written at invite time, read at acceptance to drive scoped sync, ignored thereafter.\n- Why `sendInvitationEmail` is a no-op in the Better Auth plugin and where the email actually fires from (and the resend race that motivated the returned-id assertion).\n- The nine-branch identity-aware screen and how `effectiveInvitationStatus` decides which branch renders.\n- The `updateMemberVolumeAccess` validation list and why pure validation/diff lives in `member-volume-access.ts` (testability without drizzle mocking).\n\n## Phase 3: On-Demand Modules\n\nRead entries only when your task touches the area. Grouped by theme.\n\n### Org Operations\n\nTouched together when working on admin surfaces — the People page, dashboards, billing, settings, internal-plan tooling.\n\n- **Billing**: Read `docs/billing/README.md` for the seat model and Stripe lifecycle. Read `docs/billing/stripe-integration.md` only when touching Stripe SDK calls, webhooks, or checkout. Read `docs/billing/internal-plan.md` when working on `/admin/organizations` or platform-admin bypass behavior.