ssing; route to pending_today when targetDate\n  === today and still before cron cutoff.\n\n  Point 2 (Moderate) — target_failed hard-codes reflect. Confirmed in\n  awareness-status-read.ts:72. Day-level failed_* can come from any stage.\n  Valid. Make diagnostic generic; soften the casual copy (\"卡在生成阶段\" →\n  \"没落下来\").\n\n  Point 3 (Moderate) — provider_contract semantics don't match\n  validator-rejected case. Valid and important. provider_contract elsewhere\n  means \"known deterministic failure; fallback is appropriate.\" The\n  validator-rejection path bypasses failover entirely. I considered the\n  reviewer's Option 2 (route through observed-failover) but it doesn't fit:\n  invalid_finalize_payload is a stochastic model-output issue, not a model-tier\n   capability. Retrying on a different model doesn't reliably help, so the\n  capability-cache write would record a misleading signal. Going with Option 1:\n   classify as failed_unknown. Fingerprint invalid_finalize_payload stays in\n  the attempt record for forensics; outcome class no longer lies about fallback\n   semantics.\n\n  Point 4 (Minor) — cron-hour precision. Confirmed. 23:00 cron clamped to hour\n  23 means the jitter window 23:00–24:00 is unreachable; 21:30 cron + 1h\n  returns 22, so localHour < 22 is false at 22:15 even though that's inside the\n   buffer. Valid. Switch to minute-of-day cutoff: parse both minute and hour\n  fields of the cron expression, return hour*60 + minute + 60.\n```\n\ni think you are on the same page, implement a few commits on top to address them\nwhen applicable, follow our testing standards in docs/testing.md and prompting best practices in docs/agent/prompting-guide.md if applicable. These are general best practices rather than strict requirements for all implementations. You will need to adapt them based on our specific use cases and our discussion.","I saw an external code review, is this true\n\n---\n\nserver/agent/tools/awareness-status-read.ts\n        ) {\n          facts.recentFailureCount += 1\n        }\n      }\n@cursor\ncursor Bot\n4 minutes ago\nDuplicated failure count has off-by-one window boundary\nLow Severity\n\nThe inline recent-failure counting loop duplicates the already-exported recentFailureCountInWindow from awareness-scenario (which is already imported in this file) but uses a different window boundary. The canonical function checks age >= 0 && age < windowDays (exclusive, 7-day window), while the inline code checks entry.date >= addDays(today, -7) (inclusive, effectively an 8-day window). A failure exactly 7 days ago is counted by the inline code but not by the classifier, causing facts.recentFailureCount to potentially disagree with the scenario classification it accompanies.\n","ok go ahead and fix it","Write a PR description for this work, aimed at a technical colleague who won't read the diff.\n\nFormat:\n1. Top (1–2 sentences): the direct impact in product or user-facing terms — what changed for the world, even if the work is purely technical. Lead with this.\n2. Body (3–5 sentences): the substance of what changed and why it was done this way. Mention specific components or functions only when they're load-bearing for the reader's mental model — don't enumerate them.\n\nAvoid:\n- a line-by-line or file-by-file changelog\n- references to line numbers\n- restating the obvious (e.g., \"added a function that does X\" when X was the whole point)\n\nThe reader should come away with a clear mental model of what we did and why — not how every piece works.","how would you polish my slack message here\n\n---\n\n","Okay, I sent the polished message.\n\nSince you created a local script before to test the DeepSeek provider error, can you maybe follow a similar pattern to see that, based on our current code, this problem is correctly handled?","Give me a reminder: if the user is using a Claude model, does the behavior change at all when it comes to the JSON schema structure?","So can you verify this with Claude C